================================================================
AI AND VECTOR SEARCH NOTES
================================================================

The Qdrant snapshots distributed as *.snapshot files contain
vector embeddings produced using OpenAI text-embedding-3-large
(3072-dimensional). Embeddings are derived works of the DATA and
are therefore covered by the same CC BY 4.0 licence. OpenAI's
terms of service apply to any live API calls You make; the
embeddings themselves are inert data and do not trigger ongoing
obligations to OpenAI.

The Apache-2.0 licensed adapter scripts in
"0_Workflow and Pipelines CWICR/" optionally integrate with
third-party Large Language Model APIs (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google
Generative AI, Mistral, Groq, DeepSeek) when the deploying user
configures the corresponding API keys. Prompts and context are
transmitted to the provider you selected; the deploying user is
solely responsible for (a) which providers are enabled, (b)
transfer-impact assessment when personal data is involved, and
(c) concluding EU Standard Contractual Clauses (Regulation
2021/914) or equivalent with the chosen provider(s).

================================================================
EU AI ACT TRANSPARENCY
================================================================

The AI-assisted pipelines and agent instructions distributed
with this repository include cost-estimation and classification
features. Under Article 50 of Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 (AI
Act), end users must be informed that they are interacting with
AI. Outputs are probabilistic and must be validated by a
qualified construction-estimation professional before use in any
tender, contract, or binding cost commitment.

